div.div: In terms of Java, Ad-hoc Polmorphism branches out into overloading and overriding functions and widening coercion. Universal Polymorphism branches out into covariant inclusion and use of generics types.

div.font: Polymorphism is a concept that that be implemented in many ways. That being said, different programming languages have different rules and restrictions on how Polymorphism can be implemented. We will be focusing on the concept of Polymorphism as it relates to the Java language.
